public final class Saml2IdentityProvider
extends IdentityProvider

    A special type of IdentityProvider that supports the SAML 2.0 protocol. For more information, see Identity Providers and Federation.


    Note: This model distinguishes fields that are null because they are unset from fields that are explicitly set to null. This is done in the setter methods of the Saml2IdentityProvider.Builder, which maintain a set of all explicitly set fields called __explicitlySet__. The hashCode() and equals(Object) methods are implemented to take __explicitlySet__ into account. The constructor, on the other hand, does not set __explicitlySet__ (since the constructor cannot distinguish explicit null from unset null). As a consequence, objects should always be created or deserialized using the Saml2IdentityProvider.Builder.
